sysinv/sysinv/sysinv/sysinv/common/utils.message:
There is issue with utility is_valid_boolstr -- it doesn't check the type of the provided value, so if (None, True, False, etc) are provided versus a literal string. yaml differentiates between boolean values and string so a <true> is not the same as string literal "true".

Changing to the following; note strbool can have different exceptions depending on the input.

from distutils.util import strtobool
..
def is_valid_boolstr(val):
    try:
        bool(strtobool(val))
    except Exception:
        return False
    return True

